Test file: src/claim-office.spec.ts
Failing test: "should apply 20% loyalty discount for customer with exactly 2 years — sword: 100 base - 20 loyalty + 10 first insurance + 5 fee = 95"
Expected behavior: Customers with >= 2 years get a 20% loyalty discount on the policy base premium
Current error: Expected 95, received 115
Implementation file: src/claim-office.ts

Current implementation:
```typescript
function calculateQuotePremium(items: any[]): number {
  const typeCounts = countByType(items);
  const basePremium = calculateBasePremium(typeCounts);
  const itemSurcharges = calculateItemSurcharges(items);
  const firstInsurance = basePremium * FIRST_INSURANCE_RATE;
  return Math.ceil(basePremium + itemSurcharges + firstInsurance + PROCESSING_FEE);
}

export function processScenario(scenario: any): unknown {
  const results = scenario.steps.map((step: any) => ({
    premium: calculateQuotePremium(step.items),
  }));
  return { results };
}
```

The loyalty discount is a policy-wide modifier: -20% of the policy base premium. It applies when customer.yearsWithMHPCO >= 2.

Minimal changes:
1. Pass customer info to calculateQuotePremium
2. Add loyalty discount: if yearsWithMHPCO >= 2, subtract 20% of basePremium

Formula becomes: basePremium + itemSurcharges - loyaltyDiscount + firstInsurance + PROCESSING_FEE

Make sure all existing tests still pass (they use yearsWithMHPCO: 0, so loyalty discount won't apply).

EXPERIMENT MODE: Run autonomously, proceed to Refactor after completion.

